raw_data.title: IT Project Manager
raw_data.description: This position requires the coordination and delivery of multiple, simultaneous Building Automation projects of various complexities. Manage the coordination and overall integration of technical activities in the implementation of Building Systems and Technology upgrades, retrofits and new installation projects. Direct internal and external team members, client stakeholders, subcontractors and vendors to ensure clear understanding of scope, timelines and budget requirements. Lead internal workstreams to provide exceptional deliverables that exceed project expectations. Work with various vendors, IT, and network infrastructure provisioning teams to deploy and onboard technological solutions for automation and controls required to support and maintain the client’s critical systems operations.

raw_data.description: Primary support and systems administration for desktops, servers, networks, a subset of purchased software, and wide area network systems.  The role is both client facing and internal operations support.  Troubleshoots, installs, tests, monitors, develops, and manages technology.  This is usually the entry level position to information technology at ESI, and has a wide exposure to technology.
